associated_reports.name: Email / Phone - for Status, Source, Rank
associated_reports.description: Names and emails or phone numbers for players having a specific status or method between certain dates (for example "complete") that did not have a status or method at any time in the past (for example, "opt-out")
associated_reports.sql:
select distinct m.id master_id, msid, rec_type, UPPER(LEFT(pi.first_name,1)) || LOWER(SUBSTRING(pi.first_name,2)) as first,
UPPER(LEFT(pi.last_name,1)) || LOWER(SUBSTRING(pi.last_name,2)) as last,
data 
from player_infos pi 
:filter_previous
inner join masters m on m.id = pi.master_id
inner join player_contacts pc 
on pc.master_id = pi.master_id
WHERE 
pc.rank in (:contact_rank)
AND pc.rec_type in (:rec_type)
AND ((:source) is NULL or pc.source IN (:source) )
AND pi.rank in (:player_has_rank)
AND (
  (:with_status) is null AND (:with_method) is null
  OR exists
  (select th.master_id from tracker_history th where
     th.master_id = pi.master_id and 
     (sub_process_id in (:with_status) or protocol_event_id in (:with_method) )
     and (:from_date is null or  event_date >= :from_date) 
     and (:to_date is null or event_date <= :to_date)
  )
)
AND (
  (:without_status) is null AND (:without_method) is null
  OR
  not exists
  (select th.master_id from tracker_history th where
     th.master_id = pi.master_id and 
     (sub_process_id in (:without_status) or protocol_event_id in (:without_method) )

  )
  
)

contact_rank: 
  general_selection: 
    label: Select contact records with rank  [*]
    item_type: player_contacts_rank
    multiple: multiple
    default: 
      - 10
rec_type: 
  general_selection: 
    item_type: player_contacts_type
    multiple: multiple
    label: for contact types  [*]
    default: 
      - email
      - phone


with_status: 
  sub_process: 
    label: for players having status
    all: true
    multiple: multiple
    default:
      - 39
with_method:
  protocol_event:
    label: or method
    all: true
    multiple: multiple
    default:

from_date: 
  date: 
    label: where the event date is from
    all: true
    multiple: single
to_date: 
  date: 
    label: and the event date is before
    all: true
    multiple: single

      
without_status: 
  sub_process: 
    all: true
    multiple: multiple
    label: At any time the player should not have status 
    default:
      - 45
      - 54
      - 8
without_method:
  protocol_event:
    label: and also should not have method
    all: true
    multiple: multiple
    default:   
player_has_rank:

    multiple: multiple

associated_reports.name: Name, Address or Contact
associated_reports.description:
Enter a name to find in player or pro info, a word to find anywhere in the address, or an email or phone number.
Enter first name (or initial) and last name  (separated with a space) to refine name searches.
associated_reports.sql:
select distinct m.id master_id, 
pi.first_name, pi.middle_name, pi.last_name, pi.nick_name,
pro.first_name, pro.middle_name, pro.last_name, pro.nick_name,
a.street, a.street2, a.city, a.state, a.zip, 
pc.data, pc.rec_type,
regexp_replace(:phone_or_email, '\W+', '', 'g') test
from masters m
inner join player_infos pi
on pi.master_id = m.id
left join addresses a
on m.id = a.master_id
left join pro_infos pro
on pro.master_id = m.id
left join player_contacts pc
on pc.master_id = m.id
where 
(:name is null 
or pi.first_name ~* :name
or pro.first_name ~* :name
or pi.last_name ~* :name
or pro.last_name ~* :name
or pi.middle_name ~* :name
or pro.middle_name ~* :name
or pi.nick_name ~* :name
or pro.nick_name ~* :name
or( 
    pi.first_name ~* coalesce(split_part(:name, ' ', 1),'none')
    AND pi.last_name ~* coalesce(split_part(replace(:name, '  ', ' '), ' ', 2),'none')
  )
) AND
(:phone_or_email is null 
or regexp_replace(pc.data, '\W+', '', 'g') ~* regexp_replace(:phone_or_email, '\W+', '', 'g')
)
AND
(:word_in_address is null 
or street ~* :word_in_address
or street2 ~* :word_in_address
or street3 ~* :word_in_address
or city ~* :word_in_address
or state ~* :word_in_address
or zip ~* :word_in_address
or region ~* :word_in_address
or postal_code ~* :word_in_address
)
associated_reports.search_attrs:
name: 
  text: 
    all: true
    multiple: single
word_in_address: 
  text: 
    all: true
    multiple: single


phone_or_email: 
  text: 
    all: true
    multiple: single

associated_reports.name: Updates by User
associated_reports.description: Find updated records made by a specific user in a certain date range
associated_reports.sql:
select m.id master_id, max(event_date) event_date 
from masters m 
left outer join tracker_history th1
on m.id = th1.master_id and th1.protocol_id = 4
where 
exists(
select * from player_contact_history pc
where pc.master_id = m.id
and pc.updated_at >= :since_date 
and pc.user_id = :user
)
or exists(
select * from address_history a
where a.master_id = m.id
and a.updated_at >= :since_date 
and a.user_id = :user
)
or exists(
select * from scantron_history st
where st.master_id = m.id
and st.updated_at >= :since_date 
and st.user_id = :user
)
or exists(
select * from sage_assignments sa
where sa.master_id = m.id
and sa.updated_at >= :since_date 
and sa.user_id = :user
)
or exists(
select * from tracker_history th
where th.master_id = m.id
and th.updated_at >= :since_date 
and th.user_id = :user
)
or exists(
select * from player_info_history pi
where pi.master_id = m.id
and pi.updated_at >= :since_date 
and pi.user_id = :user
)
group by m.id;
associated_reports.search_attrs:
since_date: 
  date: 
    all: true
    multiple: single
    default: -10 days
user: 
  user: 
    all: true
    multiple: single

associated_reports.name: Reused Contact Information
associated_reports.description: Check for records having contact information (email or phone) used by multiple master records
associated_reports.sql:
select master_id, data, rec_type, pc1.rank, pi.first_name, pi.last_name, pi.rank "player_rank" 
from player_contacts pc1 
inner join player_infos pi using (master_id)
where regexp_replace(data, '\W+', '', 'g') in
(
  select regexp_replace(data, '\W+', '', 'g') 
  from player_contacts pc 
  group by regexp_replace(data, '\W+', '', 'g')
  having count(distinct master_id) > 1
)
order by rec_type, data

associated_reports.name: Phone Log Follow Up
associated_reports.description:
* Select the person who was calling or who was called - select 'User' if this was a Zeus user
* For a Zeus user, optionally refine by selecting the user name
* Optionally include only records where follow up is before a specified date
* Optionally include only records where protocol is specified
associated_reports.sql:
SELECT 
  dt.master_id, first_name, last_name, 
  follow_up_when, 
  select_next_step, protocols.name,
  data, select_call_direction, 
  select_who, users.email username, 
  called_when, select_result
FROM (
 SELECT 
   master_id, 
  follow_up_when, data,select_call_direction, 
  select_who, called_when, select_result, select_next_step, protocol_id, user_id,
   rank()
 OVER (
  PARTITION BY master_id 
  ORDER BY called_when DESC, id DESC
 ) AS r
 FROM activity_log_player_contact_phones
) AS dt
INNER JOIN player_infos pi
ON pi.master_id = dt.master_id
INNER JOIN users
ON dt.user_id = users.id
LEFT OUTER JOIN protocols
ON dt.protocol_id = protocols.id
WHERE
  r = 1
AND 
  (
    select_next_step IN ('call back', 'more info requested')
    OR follow_up_when IS NOT NULL
  )
AND
 (:protocol IS NULL OR protocol_id = :protocol)
AND
 ( 
  :select_who IS NULL OR 
  :select_who <> 'user' AND select_who = :select_who OR
  :select_who = 'user' AND select_who = :select_who AND (:username IS NULL OR dt.user_id = :username)
 )
AND
 (:follow_up_before IS NULL OR follow_up_when <= :follow_up_before)
ORDER BY
  follow_up_when DESC, called_when ASC
;
associated_reports.search_attrs:
select_who: 
  general_selection: 
    item_type: activity_log__player_contact_phone_select_who
    multiple: single
    label: Filter by Person
    default: user

username: 
  user: 
    all: true
    multiple: single
    label: if 'User' select Username to refine the filter
    default: current_user

follow_up_before: 
  date: 
    all: true
    multiple: single
    label: follow up before (optional)
    default: now
protocol: 
  protocol: 
    all: true
    multiple: single
    label: linked to protocol (optional)

associated_reports.name: Phone Log Report
associated_reports.description: Simple report of Phone Log activity in a date range. Both the start and end dates are optional.
associated_reports.sql:
select 
dt.master_id,
protocols.name,
pi.first_name,
pi.last_name,
dt.data phone,
dt.select_call_direction,
dt.select_who,
users.email,
dt.called_when,
dt.select_result,
dt.select_next_step,
dt.follow_up_when,
dt.notes


FROM  activity_log_player_contact_phones dt
INNER JOIN player_infos pi
ON pi.master_id = dt.master_id
INNER JOIN users
ON dt.user_id = users.id
LEFT OUTER JOIN protocols
ON dt.protocol_id = protocols.id
where 
(:called_from is null OR called_when >= :called_from)
 AND
(:called_to is null OR called_when <= :called_to)
associated_reports.search_attrs:
called_from: 
  date: 
    all: true
    multiple: single
called_to: 
  date: 
    all: true
    multiple: single

associated_reports.name: IPA Recruitment Ranks
associated_reports.description: List potential IPA subjects by IPA recruitment rank
associated_reports.sql:
select distinct r.master_id, pi.first_name, pi.last_name, r.rank
from ipa_recruitment_ranks r
inner join player_infos pi 
on pi.master_id = r.master_id
where
(:include_ranks) is null or r.rank in (:include_ranks)
AND
(
  (:does_not_have_status) is null 
  OR 
  r.master_id not in
  ( 
    select distinct th.master_id
    from tracker_history th
    where th.sub_process_id in (:does_not_have_status)
  )
)
AND
(
  (:has_status) is null 
  OR 
  r.master_id in
  ( 
    select distinct th.master_id
    from tracker_history th
    where th.sub_process_id in (:has_status)
  )
)
;
associated_reports.search_attrs:
include_ranks: 
  general_selection: 
    item_type: dynamic_model__ipa_recruitment_ranks_rank
    label: Have any of these ranks
    multiple: multiple
    default: 
      - 0
      - 1
      - 2
      - 3
      - 4


does_not_have_status: 
  sub_process: 
    label: AND DO NOT have any of these statuses (optional)
    all: true
    multiple: multiple
    default: 
      - 92
      - 93

    all: true
